CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 27, 1958, pg. 28, reads: "Riding in Style - Thousands of Pittsburghers formed a cheering throng of humanity on Downtown streets Monday afternoon as the second-place Pittsburgh Pirates were honored with a mammoth parade.  Among the Pirates receiving cheers along the parade route were Nellie King and R. C. Stevens, left photo... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Convertible car in parade honoring Pittsburgh Pirates with baseball players R. C. Stevens seated behind driver, and Nellie King seated behind front passenger seat, in front of People's First National Bank, Downtown
